{
  "stem": "18626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean they didn't have no weapons, the Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They just had like a little police club, a piece of wood, or a piece a leather strap.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were powerful enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A Jewish policeman could, if you didn't go to work, they could have gone to the committee, and tell Dr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Elkes or the other people that family refuses to go to work, one day, another day, and then the committee says, listen.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If you got to take a little stronger force, a couple of slaps or a kick, you've got to do it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I used to work, in the beginning, to go-- we were taken to the airport too, till they established-- and they developed what's called werkstatten, the ghetto werkstatten.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That means working shops, for the Third Reich, for the German Army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they developed big factories in the ghetto was established.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all-- and it was an order, after it was all organized to make all the shops in the ghetto cabinet work, furniture makers, tailors, shoemakers, toy makers, laundry factories to wash for the Germans their laundry, for the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All was established in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was given orders by the Jewish Committee, anybody who was a tailor, anybody who was a shoemaker, anybody who was a wood turner, anybody who's a cabinet maker should register to the committee.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you are going to get an Ausweis, that means a card, a working card that you are working in the ghetto shops, you understand?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you don't have to go no more to the airfields, airport, to do the hard rough labor work, you understand?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I registered.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know too much wood-turning.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
